<Base title="About SalaryTools.us – Free US Salary Calculators" description="SalaryTools.us provides free salary calculators for US workers. Hourly to salary converter and take-home pay calculator with all 50 states.">
<div class="container" style="max-width:680px;padding-top:4rem;padding-bottom:5rem;">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>About SalaryTools.us</h1>
    <p>SalaryTools.us provides free salary calculators built specifically for US workers. Our tools help employees, freelancers, and job seekers understand their pay — before and after taxes.</p>
    <h2>Our tools</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/">Hourly to Salary Calculator</a> — convert any hourly rate to annual, monthly, biweekly, and weekly pay with overtime and PTO support</li>
      <li><a href="/salary-calculator">Take-Home Pay Calculator</a> — see your exact paycheck after federal tax, state tax, Social Security, Medicare, 401k, and health insurance for all 50 states</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Why we built this</h2>
    <p>Most US salary calculators are cluttered with ads, require sign-ups, or show outdated tax rates. We built clean, fast, accurate tools that work instantly on any device — no account needed.</p>
    <h2>Accuracy</h2>
    <p>Tax calculations are updated for the 2025 tax year using current IRS brackets, standard deductions, and FICA rates. State tax rates are approximations based on published flat or effective rates. For complex tax situations, consult a CPA.</p>
    <h2>Free forever</h2>
    <p>All tools are free. We earn through non-intrusive display advertising. Your salary data never leaves your browser.</p>
